        "bodyContent": "<p>The ATI TEAS 7 (Test of Essential Academic Skills) is the entrance exam that many nursing and allied health programs use to check whether you’re ready for the heavy science and math you’ll see in school. Rather than testing how “smart” you are, it looks at whether your foundation is strong enough to handle nursing coursework.</p><p>The exam is built around four major skill areas:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Reading</strong> – understanding passages, charts, and written instructions</p></li><li><p><strong>Math</strong> – working with numbers, ratios, percentages, and word problems</p></li><li><p><strong>Science</strong> – core Anatomy &amp; Physiology, biology, chemistry, and scientific reasoning</p></li><li><p><strong>English &amp; Language Usage</strong> – grammar, punctuation, spelling, and word choice in context</p></li></ul><p>Schools combine your TEAS score with your GPA, prerequisite grades, and sometimes an interview or essay. A stronger TEAS result doesn’t magically guarantee you a spot, but it often moves your application into the “take a serious look at this student” pile.</p><table style=\"min-width: 75px;\"><colgroup><col style=\"min-width: 25px;\"><col style=\"min-width: 25px;\"><col style=\"min-width: 25px;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Teas</p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Hero</p></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Test</p></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>12</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>123</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>123</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>123</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>1234</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>1234</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><img class=\"custom-image\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"technomind\" data-align=\"center\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\"></p>",
